    "html":  "\u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.8px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eDaily Economic Briefing\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003ch2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eWednesday, 10 June 2026\u003c/h2\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap;\"\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(248,113,113,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.25); color:#f87171; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eCPI DAY\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eMOVE 76.98 Drift\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSOFR 3.63% Healthy\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eNFCI \u0026#8722;0.490 Loose\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128202; Liquidity \u0026amp; Stress Metrics \u0026#8212; The \u0026quot;Gnosis\u0026quot; Pulse\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eTracking the underlying macro engine on CPI day, under the Warsh Fed regime. Current regime: Loose \u0026amp; Volatile (the bullet-train transition).\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:right; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eValue\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMarket Context\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eMOVE Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#fbbf24; font-weight:700;\"\u003e76.98\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eVolatility absorption: fixed-income desks adjust premium models ahead of today\u0026#39;s critical CPI print. Drifted up to 76.98 but remains contained beneath the active structural alert threshold.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eTerm Premium Drift\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eSOFR Rate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e3.63%\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eInterbank wholesale funding pipelines are clear; secured overnight funding execution remains frictionless, supporting the broad structural liquidity expansion.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eHealthy\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eNFCI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#60a5fa; font-weight:700;\"\u003e\u0026#8722;0.490\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eWeekly benchmark pinned deep near historic expansionary extremes. Sub-indicators show shadow macro liquidity and interbank credit lines are fully lubricated.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eLoose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"margin-top:16px; padding:14px 16px; background:rgba(96,165,250,0.06); border-left:3px solid #60a5fa; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eGnosis Interpretation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003eThe \u0026quot;Bullet Train\u0026quot; transition rules remain dominant. While bond volatility shows a minor upward drift to 76.98 from tactical positioning ahead of the CPI print, the NFCI at \u0026#8722;0.490 confirms the foundational liquidity floor is intact. Term-premium discovery should not be confused with a systemic liquidity freeze \u0026#8212; with credit pipelines clear, immediate fixed-income volatility forces capital out of defensive bonds and vents it back into equities. Intraday pullbacks are purely mechanical.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-06-10\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eHigh-impact macro windows for today\u0026#39;s CPI session. US May CPI and Real Earnings (BLS, 08:30 ET), the US Treasury 10-Year Note Auction (standard 13:00 ET) and the Monthly Treasury Statement (~14:00 ET) verified against standard BLS / Treasury release windows.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eNotes\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May CPI (MoM / YoY)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eCritical\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eCore systemic inflation print (BLS, 08:30 ET). Desks front-running via options skews; focus on core services and trimmed-mean proxies.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS Real Earnings (MoM)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eBLS companion to CPI, 08:30 ET. Purchasing-power read supplementary to the primary inflation path.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS 10-Year Note Auction\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e13:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e01:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eTreasury 10-year note auction, standard 13:00 ET. Direct test of macro term-premium appetite right after the CPI release.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS Monthly Budget Statement\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e14:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e02:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eTreasury Monthly Treasury Statement, ~14:00 ET. Fiscal deficit tracking; relevant to the fiscal-dominance debate.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eMajor Macro Horizons (CPI / FOMC)\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe CPI Threshold:\u003c/strong\u003e Today\u0026#39;s session centers on the 20:30 GMT+8 inflation print. Desks operate under a framework where spot indicators and trimmed proxies override legacy, lagging statistical weights.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe FOMC Shadow:\u003c/strong\u003e Markets are heavily anticipating the June 16\u0026#8211;17 FOMC meeting \u0026#8212; Kevin Warsh\u0026#39;s first as Fed chair \u0026#8212; expected to restructure Fed communication models.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(239,68,68,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#f87171; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eTrump \u0026amp; The Iran Situation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Ceasefire Battleground:\u003c/strong\u003e After a weekend flare-up (a Hezbollah rocket salvo, an Israeli strike on Beirut, and a 10-missile Iranian retaliation), Trump intervened, warning PM Netanyahu he would be \u0026quot;on his own\u0026quot; if he launched further counter-strikes. A pause in tit-for-tat strikes has resumed.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Total-Victory Declaration:\u003c/strong\u003e Despite the fragile truce, Trump publicly predicted a \u0026quot;total victory\u0026quot; over Iran within two weeks as talks continue through Pakistani mediators. Treat as narrative.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Bond-Vigilante Handcuff:\u003c/strong\u003e Iran is attempting to condition a Strait of Hormuz reopening on a transit-fee structure with Oman. Brent crude anchored near $92/bbl strips speculative heat from the inflation transmission pipeline.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Kevin Warsh Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Productivity Thesis:\u003c/strong\u003e Sworn in May 22, 2026, Warsh anchors his rate framework to the thesis that AI-driven productivity gains are a permanent disinflationary counterweight, letting the economy expand without traditional inflation.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStrategic Ambiguity \u0026amp; The 20-Year Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Leaks indicate Warsh plans to downplay the SEP dot plots and reduce speeches. The structural precedent of an easing window in a new Chair\u0026#39;s first 12 months sets up a sharp back-end repricing for rates desks. Treat as narrative, not confirmed guidance.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix:\u003c/strong\u003e The breakout matrix established when the April 28th swing high was cleared on April 30th \u0026#8212; validated by the May 1st expansion candle taking out the monthly high \u0026#8212; remains the technical anchor. Near-term volatility behaves as a mechanical pullback, not a structural reversal.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Levels:\u003c/strong\u003e Gnosis projections remain locked on the year-end Wall Street High Call of 8,447\u0026#8211;8,477 on S\u0026amp;P 500 futures.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e During the heavy 20:30 GMT+8 CPI window, monitor the 1.5k volume chart in MotiveWave for expansionary stop-hunts. With the architecture in a daily bull trend, do not short or fade all-time-high expansions; execute sharp liquidity flushes into the Value Area Low (VAL) cleanly as core structural buying opportunities.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Williams Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Keep position sizing tightly disciplined relative to the broader cycle as we move toward the June 16th window \u0026#8212; the formation of the ultimate, sustainable natural-cycle base for the next expansion.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
